service.name: Crisis Payment
service.description: Crisis Payment (CrP) is a one-off, non-taxable payment that is designed to help new and existing Department of Human Services customers who are in severe financial hardship and identifying customers who may qualify for CrP under the released prisoner or extreme circumstances categories.

Dimension.name: Migrants, refugees & visitors
Dimension.desc: We provide a range of payments and services if you have an eligible visa and you are Living in Australia, including support to help you with the cost of raising children and looking after dependants.

Dimension.name: Centrelink
Dimension.desc: Delivering a range of payments and services for people at times of major change.

Dimension.name: Human Services
Dimension.desc: We deliver social and health-related payments and services
